    <h1 class="section-title">Averburg</h1>
    <p>
      Nestled in the rolling hills of Averland, where the Blue Reach winds its crystal waters beneath the shadow of the World's Edge Mountains, Averburg stands as a bastion of faith and commerce. A crucial gateway between the Empire and the eastern lands, it prospers through trade—its markets bustling with fine Averland cattle, dwarven-forged steel, and exotic goods. Yet, danger lurks in the nearby Black Fire Pass, where greenskins and brigands threaten the town’s peace.
    </p>
    <p>
      Ruled by the noble House von Heldenherz, Averburg is fortified by sturdy walls, a vigilant garrison, and the Knights of Sigmar’s Blood. The Great Chapel of Sigmar towers at its heart, a beacon of devotion, while whispers of dark omens—disappearances, eerie lights, and growing orc warbands—test the town’s resolve. Still, under Count Leopold von Heldenherz, Averburg remains a defiant bulwark of steel and faith.
    </p>
